<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="254" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="5.[2080,2675,452,875]" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2082,2237,452,481]" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Richardson, 1829" authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="1829" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Geomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="umbrinus">Geomys umbrinus Richardson, 1829</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation pageId="5" pageNumber="254">“Cadadaguois, a town in southwestern part of Louisiana.” Corrected by V. Bailey in 1906 to the “Boca del Monte, Vera Cruz, Mexico.”</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[2080,2675,452,875]" lastBlockId="5.[1460,2674,880,2884]" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">
Placed into subgenus Megascapheus. Molecular studies show 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="1829" box="[2392,2553,685,718]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Geomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="umbrinus">7. umbrinus</taxonomicName>
to be a member of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="1829" box="[2308,2463,728,757]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Geomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="umbrinus">7. umbrinus</taxonomicName>
species group, which also includes 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1898" box="[2371,2535,767,796]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Thomomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atrovarius">71. atrovarius</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wied-Neuwied" authorityYear="1839" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Thomomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sheldoni">T. sheldoni</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mathis et al., 2013" authorityName="Mathis et al." authorityYear="2013" box="[2192,2358,807,836]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Thomomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nayarensis">T. nayarensis</taxonomicName>
. Thirty-two subspecies were listed by J. L. Patton in 1999 and 23 were recognized by Patton in 2005, but subsequent elevation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1898" box="[2357,2518,880,913]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Thomomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atrovarius">T. atrovarius</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wied-Neuwied" authorityYear="1839" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Thomomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sheldoni">T. sheldoni</taxonomicName>
to species rank, followed by a systematic revision of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="1829" box="[2249,2402,920,953]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Geomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="umbrinus">7. umbrinus</taxonomicName>
by V. L. Mathis and colleagues in 2014 reduced the number of subspecies considerably. Four subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
